# Logico — Project Overview

## Architecture
**Monorepo (no workspace tooling)** — two independent npm projects side by side:
- `client/` — React 19 + TypeScript + Vite frontend
- `server/` — Express 4 + Node.js (JavaScript, CommonJS) backend
- Communication: REST API at `/api/v1/` + WebSocket for AI chat

## Backend Tech Stack
- **Runtime/Framework:** Node.js + Express 4 (JavaScript, CommonJS)
- **DB/ORM:** PostgreSQL 15 + Sequelize 6 (`sequelize.define()` pattern, NOT class-based)
- **Auth:** Passport.js + JWT (stateless), 2FA via speakeasy (TOTP)
- **Validation:** Joi 17 (route-level schemas in `validations/`)
- **Security:** helmet, xss-clean, express-rate-limit, cors
- **Logging:** winston (`logger.*`) + morgan — NO `console.log`
- **AI:** OpenAI SDK + MCP (Model Context Protocol) + WebSocket agent
- **Testing:** Jest 26 + Supertest

## Frontend Tech Stack
- **Framework:** React 19 + TypeScript ~5.7 (strict mode) + Vite 6
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS v4 + shadcn/ui (new-york style, slate base)
- **Routing:** React Router DOM v7 (lazy-loaded routes)
- **Server state:** TanStack React Query v5
- **Client state:** Zustand v5 (with persist middleware for tokens only)
- **Forms:** React Hook Form v7 + Zod
- **HTTP:** Axios with interceptor-based token refresh

## Server Folder Structure
```
server/src/
├── agents/          AI agent class + WebSocket handler
├── config/          App config, passport, cors, logger, permissions.json
├── controllers/     Thin route handlers (no business logic)
├── db/              Sequelize instance
├── jobs/            Scheduled jobs (node-schedule)
├── mcp/             MCP client/server/tools
├── middlewares/     auth, validate, error, activity-logger, rateLimiter
├── models/          Sequelize models + plugins (paginate, hierarchy, toJSON)
├── routes/v1/       Express routers grouped by domain
├── seeders/         Data seeders
├── services/        Business logic (pure async functions, no classes)
├── templates/       Handlebars PDF templates
├── utils/           ApiError, catchAsync, pick, paginate, code-generator
└── validations/     Joi schemas grouped by domain
```

## Client Folder Structure
```
client/src/
├── api/services/    React Query hooks per resource
├── components/
│   ├── ui/                 shadcn/ui raw components (don't modify)
│   ├── chroma-components/  custom project components
│   ├── advance-table-grid/ reusable data table
│   ├── chroma-form/        dynamic form renderer
│   └── ai/                 AI chat components
├── pages/<domain>/<resource>/  list.tsx / details.tsx
├── routes/          RouterData[] definitions with meta.permission
├── store/           Zustand stores
└── types/           global-types.ts + domain-level .d.ts files
```

## Domain Groupings
All code is consistently grouped by these domains:
- `user-management` (users, roles, permissions)
- `configurations` → `masterdata` (brands, categories, etc.) + `products`
- `system` (activity logs, settings)
- `auth`
- `ai-agent-services`
